<h1 style="color: #1f4e79; text-align: left; clear: both;">1. Introduction</h1>
<b style="color: #1f4e79;">1.1 Purpose:</b>  
The purpose of this iFlow is to automate the process of retrieving emails from a specified Gmail inbox and sending them to a designated recipient via SMTP. The integration is triggered by a scheduled event that polls the inbox for unread emails. The desired technical outcome is to ensure that all unread emails are processed and forwarded to the specified recipient, thereby streamlining communication and ensuring that important messages are not overlooked.

<b style="color: #1f4e79;">1.2 Scope:</b>  
This integration includes the following components:
- **Sender Endpoint:** IMAP adapter configured to connect to Gmail for retrieving unread emails.
- **Receiver Endpoint:** SMTP adapter configured to send emails to the specified recipient.
- **Data Transformation Logic:** Groovy script for processing the email content and modifying headers before sending.
- **Target Systems:** Gmail (for receiving emails) and SMTP server (for sending emails).
  
Exclusions include any handling of attachments beyond forwarding the email body and headers, as well as any error handling mechanisms that are not explicitly defined in this document.

<h1 style="color: #1f4e79; text-align: left; clear: both;">2. Integration Overview</h1>
<b style="color: #1f4e79;">2.1 Integration Architecture:</b>  
```mermaid
graph TD;
    A[Start Event] --> B[Retrieve Emails from Gmail];
    B --> C[Process Email with Groovy Script];
    C --> D[Modify Email Content];
    D --> E[Send Email via SMTP];
    E --> F[End Event];
```

<b style="color: #1f4e79;">2.2 Integration Components:</b>  
| Component                | Role                          | Details                                                                 |
|--------------------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| IMAP Adapter (Sender)    | Retrieve Emails               | Connects to Gmail to fetch unread emails from the inbox.                |
| SMTP Adapter (Receiver)   | Send Emails                   | Sends processed emails to the specified recipient using SMTP protocol.   |
| Groovy Script            | Process Email Content         | Contains logic to modify email headers and body before sending.         |
| Content Modifier         | Modify Email Headers          | Sets the subject header and other properties for the outgoing email.     |

<h1 style="color: #1f4e79; text-align: left; clear: both;">3. Integration Scenarios</h1>
<b style="color: #1f4e79;">3.1 Scenario Description:</b>  
1. **Start Event:** The integration process begins with a scheduled trigger that initiates the polling of the Gmail inbox.
2. **Retrieve Emails:** The IMAP adapter connects to the Gmail inbox and retrieves unread emails.
3. **Process Email:** The Groovy script processes the retrieved email content, extracting necessary information such as the subject and body.
4. **Modify Email Content:** The Content Modifier updates the email headers, particularly the subject, to ensure clarity for the recipient.
5. **Send Email:** The SMTP adapter sends the modified email to the designated recipient.
6. **End Event:** The process concludes after the email has been sent.

<b style="color: #1f4e79;">3.2 Data Flows:</b>  
- **Input:** Unread emails from the Gmail inbox.
- **Processing:** Email content is processed and modified using Groovy script and Content Modifier.
- **Output:** Emails sent to the specified recipient via SMTP.

<b style="color: #1f4e79;">3.3 Security Requirements:</b>  
- Use of secure connections (IMAPS for retrieving emails and STARTTLS for sending emails).
- Authentication credentials must be securely managed and not hardcoded in the scripts.

<h1 style="color: #1f4e79; text-align: left; clear: both;">4. Error Handling and Logging</h1>  
Error handling will be implemented to log any failures during the email retrieval or sending process. All events will be logged as per the configuration in the iFlow properties.

<h1 style="color: #1f4e79; text-align: left; clear: both;">5. Testing Validation</h1>  
| Test Case ID | Scenario                        | Expected Outcome                                      |
|--------------|----------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| TC_01        | Retrieve unread emails           | Unread emails are successfully retrieved from Gmail. |
| TC_02        | Process email content            | Email content is correctly processed and modified.   |
| TC_03        | Send email via SMTP             | Email is successfully sent to the recipient.         |
